  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package carries a decision of Accepted; however, two credibility factors (Model form and Equivalency of input parameters) are recorded without requiredLevel or achievedLevel, leaving the acceptance decision without complete structured factor grounding — a W-CON-01 factor-decision inconsistency.",
