      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs must be characterized with uncertainty bounds; probability distributions must be assigned for Monte Carlo propagation; sources of input data must be traceable.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity and density assigned normal distributions based on literature. Power-law hemolysis model constants (C, alpha, beta) assigned uniform distributions with wide bounds due to limited donor-specific data. Achieved level 2 due to uncharacterized inter-donor variability."
